HEADWORD: Diluvian
<hw>Di*lu"vi*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>diluvien</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to a deluge, esp. to
the Noachian deluge; diluvial; <as>as, of <ex>diluvian</ex>
origin</as>.</def> <rj><au>Buckland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

